assacre, also called Rape of Nanjing (December 1937–January 1938), was the mass killing and the ravaging of Chinese citizens and capit...</div></div></a></div><div class="slide b_crslitm b_sldfitcont" data-dataurl="" data-rinterval="" data-appns="SERP" data-k="5732.1" data-tag="" style="" tabindex="0" data-mini="" role="listitem"><a class="b_aatclink" tabindex="-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&amp;&amp;p=acc375a76eea0d7dd006b74ce203728e3d9814b19f11b9ae473e241f32b88c44JmltdHM9MTc3MzAxNDQwMA&amp;ptn=3&amp;ver=2&amp;hsh=4&amp;fclid=3cea4449-7429-6cb5-1a15-51ed75be6d5d&amp;psq=Japanese+troops+entering+Nanjing+on+December+13%2c+1937&amp;u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnJpdGFubmljYS5jb20vZXZlbnQvTmFuamluZy1NYXNzYWNyZQ&amp;ntb=1" h="ID=SERP,5565.1"><div class="b_insideSlide"><div class="b_title">How many people were killed during the Nanjing Massacre?</div><div class="b_text">Estimates of the number of Chinese killed in the Nanjing Massacre range from 100,000 to more than 300,000.</div></div></a></div><div class="slide b_crslitm b_sldfitcont" data-dataurl="" data-rinterval="" data-appns="SERP" data-k="5733.1" data-tag="" style="" tabindex="0" data-mini="" role="listitem"><a class="b_aatclink" tabindex="-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&amp;&amp;p=acc375a76eea0d7dd006b74ce203728e3d9814b19f11b9ae473e241f32b88c44JmltdHM9MTc3MzAxNDQwMA&amp;ptn=3&amp;ver=2&amp;hsh=4&amp;fclid=3cea4449-7429-6cb5-1a15-51ed75be6d5d&amp;psq=Japanese+troops+entering+Nanjing+on+December+13%2c+1937&amp;u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnJpdGFubmljYS5jb20vZXZlbnQvTmFuamluZy1NYXNzYWNyZQ&amp;ntb=1" h="ID=SERP,5567.1"><div class="b_insideSlide"><div class="b_title">Who ordered the Nanjing Massacre?</div><div class="b_text">The destruction of Nanjing was ordered by Matsui Iwane, commanding general of the Japanese Central China Front Army. Japanese soldiers carried out...</div></div></a></div><div class="slide b_crslitm b_sldfitcont" data-dataurl="" data-rinterval="" data-appns="SERP" data-k="5734.1" data-tag="" style="" tabindex="0" data-mini="" role="listitem"><a class="b_aatclink" tabindex="-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&amp;&amp;p=acc375a76eea0d7dd006b74ce203728e3d9814b19f11b9ae473e241f32b88c44JmltdHM9MTc3MzAxNDQwMA&amp;ptn=3&amp;ver=2&amp;hsh=4&amp;fclid=3cea4449-7429-6cb5-1a15-51ed75be6d5d&amp;psq=Japanese+troops+entering+Nanjing+on+December+13%2c+1937&amp;u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnJpdGFubmljYS5jb20vZXZlbnQvTmFuamluZy1NYXNzYWNyZQ&amp;ntb=1" h="ID=SERP,5569.1"><div class="b_insideSlide"><div class="b_title">What happened to Matsui Iwane and Tani Hisao?</div><div class="b_text">Shortly after the end of World War II, Matsui Iwane and Tani Hisao, a lieutenant general who had personally participated in acts of murder and rape...</div></div></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></li><li class="b_algo" data-id="" iid="SERP.5735" data-bm="11"><div class="b_tpcn"><a class="tilk" aria-label="fandom.com" redirecturl="" tabindex="-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&amp;&amp;p=94a468634ca82fa963255235dc38a35a813af6904b55f9da36d137c2f8c5f06cJmltdHM9MTc3MzAxNDQwMA&amp;ptn=3&amp;ver=2&amp;hsh=4&amp;fclid=3cea4449-7429-6cb5-1a15-51ed75be6d5d&amp;psq=Japanese+troops+entering+Nanjing+on+December+13%2c+1937&amp;u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9taWxpdGFyeS1oaXN0b3J5LmZhbmRvbS5jb20vd2lraS9CYXR0bGVfb2ZfTmFua2luZw&amp;ntb=1" h="ID=SERP,5269.1"><div class="tpic"><div class="wr_fav" data-priority="2"><div class="cico siteicon" style="width:32px;height:32px;"><img src="./Japanese troops entering Nanjing on December 13, 1937 - Search_files/ODF(12).9CqnaYA4Ez_xJSikkft7Hw" height="32" width="32" alt="Global web icon" class="rms_img" data-bm="64"></div></div></div><div class="tptxt"><div class="tptt">fandom.com</div><div class="tpmeta"><div class="b_attribution" tabindex="-1"><cite>https://military-history.fandom.com › wiki › Battle_of_Nanking</cite></div></div></div></a></div><h2 class=""><a target="_blank" href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&a